ble-counting. (5) CROWDED TRADE RISK — a 49.1% TTF spike and a 5.82% Henry Hub spike on March 2 means every algorithmic momentum system globally is already long natural gas. Mean reversion from crowded geopolitical trades is historically violent and fast. The dominant agent is Sentiment at confidence 0.51 — barely above coin-flip. Entering a commodity trade on a 0.51 consensus confidence in a RANGE_BOUND technical regime, after the catalyzing event is already priced, with maximum export infrastructure utilization preventing physical transmission, with domestic fundamentals structurally bearish, and with peace-talk risk capable of collapsing the entire thesis overnight, violates basic risk management discipline. The asymmetry is unfavorable: upside requires multiple bullish assumptions to hold simultaneously; downside requires only one bearish scenario to materialize. WAIT for: (a) a Henry Hub pullback toward $2.80-$2.83 support that provides better risk/reward, (b) evidence that Qatar shutdown duration extends beyond 2 weeks (confirming supply disruption persistence), (c) TTF stabilizing above €50/MWh post-shock (confirming European premium is structural not ephemeral), and (d) at least one EIA storage report showing a tighter-than-expected withdrawal post-shock before entering. Current entry at $2.977 is a FOMO entry into a post-event spike.
